Stormtroopers are the elite shock troopers of the Galactic Empire. Like Imperial-class Star Destroyers and TIE Fighters, stormtroopers served as reminders of the Emperor's power, extensions of his will, and a method of keeping the Empire's thousands of star systems in line through fear.

This armor is white plastoid-composite body armor over a sealed black body glove. In this respect it appears similar to the armor worn by their predecessors of the Clone Wars. The complete ensemble encases the body, and typically has no individually distinguishing marking outside of rank, so much so that casual first-time observers would sometimes mistake the stormtroopers for some form of battle droids.

The armor also protects the troopers from very harsh environments as well as projectiles and impact weapons. The armor might be penetrated by a direct blaster bolt, but would significantly reduce damage from the absorbed bolt. Blast energy sinks were distributed around the armor to absorb energy from a blaster bolt. The insulated body glove allowed for comfortable operations in an very wide range of climates, including even total vacuum conditions, or immense extremes of cold and heat. In this respect, it could be argued that the armor is much less suited to battle than it's clone armor predecessor, and much more suitable as a high-tech survival suit.

There are a variety of different kinds of armor intended to defend against the harsh enviroments of space, deflect the impact of blaster bolts and protect versus all types of damage that can be found on a battlefield. These suits are usually built in with a personal shield generator.

The E-11 blaster rifle is a blaster rifle manufactured by BlasTech Industries during the Galactic Civil War. It is the standard blaster rifle of the Imperial stormtroopers. A powerful, light and compact weapon, the E-11 is used widely through the galaxy.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

Power paks or power cells provide energy for many vehicles, and small blaster weapons. Most power cells contain concentrated amounts of gases that, when heated, form plasma. In small blasters, power cells are used to create blaster bolts that are not nearly as powerful as blasters using a combination of magazines containing gases (that after being heated would change into plasma) and proper Blaster power packs. A small power cell could be used to power a prosthetic without the need for recharging.

The Service Special is a small blaster used by Imperial law enforcement officers.

Developed around 4 BBY, the Service Special is only half the size of most blasters but possesses six times the power, and is a secret even from some elements of the Imperial military. Its power is roughly equal to one of the four cannons in the Millennium Falcon's quad-guns.

These troops were descendants of the Republic shock troopers of the Grand Army of the Republic during the Clone Wars. During the height of the Clone Wars, the unit maintained law and order on the capital world, and was led by Clone Commander Fox.                                                                                                                                     In the time of the Galactic Empire, under Palpatine's issue of martial law and sweeping emergency powers, the Coruscant Guards were empowered to search any facility or dwelling, arrest any citizen, and locate and detain suspected criminals and Rebel agents. These elite troops rarely saw combat, and were instead strictly for police service. They were in almost all Coruscant's districts and many of them were assigned to watch the city planet's sewers.

The Imperial Guard's Armor is light yet heavily padded crimson and black armor that provides protection against physical attacks. Their sophisticated battle helmet, which is lined with advanced sensors, allows them to work in complete darkness, and also contains a comlink scrambler for communication with fellow personnel. A unit commander's helmet is also equipped with a voice activated heads-up display that shows Coruscant Guard positions. Optional tracking beacon software lets a unit commander know the whereabouts of his subordinates at all times.

A unit commander's helmet is also equipped with a voice activated heads-up display that shows Coruscant Guard positions. Optional tracking beacon software lets a unit commander know the whereabouts of his subordinates at all times.

The A280 is a blaster rifle produced by BlasTech Industries and is considered to be one of the best armor-piercing blasters produced.

Though much heavier than Imperial-issue rifles such as the E-11, the A280 is a sturdy weapon and is reputed to be able to cut a fully-armored stormtrooper in half at medium range. This weapon, along with its predecessor, the DLT-20A, were marketed as Longblasters. The A280 was different from the DLT-20A in that its galven circuits were clustered near the focusing crystal, giving the weapon a slight bulge at the midsection. This also provided the A280 with more power over a longer range.

A blaster is a ranged weapon that fires bursts of particle beam energy called blaster bolts from a replaceable power cell. The most commonly used weapon in the Galaxy, blasters' intense beams consisting of compacted high-energy particles and intense light can kill or paralyze their target, depending on their setting.

Exchange Negotiators are a type of energy baton used by the criminal organization known as the Exchange. They are presumably used to "negotiate" prices with buyers, or perhaps the name is just a cover-up of the weapon's real use. The negotiator delivers a more potent shock than other stun batons.

A stun baton is a nonlethal short-range melee weapon that immobilizes organic targets with a powerful electrical shock. It requires the user to physically touch the target in order to immobilize them effectively.

Phase II incorporates all of its predecessor's systems in addition to polarized lenses, padding, sensors, and stronger, lighter armor plates. It can also support more modular attachments, making it infinitely superior to its the Phase I version. It is far more comfortable to wear as well, since the Kaminoans had become more familiar with Human anatomy. Unlike the Phase I armor, color was used to denote unit affiliation, not rank.

There are a variety of different kinds of armor intended to defend against the harsh enviroments of space, deflect the impact of blaster bolts and protect versus all types of damage that can be found on a battlefield. These suits are usually built in with a personal shield generator.

The Firelance is a lightweight blaster rifle with a very effective stun setting. It was marketed to "freelance law enforcement officials" who needed to bring their prey back alive.

Power paks or power cells provide energy for many vehicles, and small blaster weapons. Most power cells contain concentrated amounts of gases that, when heated, form plasma. In small blasters, power cells are used to create blaster bolts that are not nearly as powerful as blasters using a combination of magazines containing gases (that after being heated would change into plasma) and proper Blaster power packs. A small power cell could be used to power a prosthetic without the need for recharging.

This holdout blaster pistol, sometimes known as a scout blaster, is a standard-issue weapon used by the scout troopers of the Galactic Empire. Clone scout troopers of the 41st Elite Legion were also known to carry these weapons during the latter stages of the Clone Wars.

This compact, one-handed blaster is fitted with a side-mounted targeting scope and phase amplifier, and featured a miniature gas cell on the rear. The weapon had a short-range barrel. Scout troopers commonly carry these weapons in a boot holster. Because scout troopers wore padded gloves, the pistol has a pressure-sensitive stock rather than a trigger. The trooper is able to grip the stock with two gloved fingers through the enlarged finger guard.
